Defendant Nikolas W Malvick in court with attorney Kelsey Morin.  Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Amended information filed by the State.  Defendant pleads guilty to Counts 1 and 2.  Court finds the defendant guilty of counts 1 and 2.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Morin makes statements.  Defendant makes statements. 

The Court Orders the Following:  Count # 1 

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
6 months Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  (Credit - 0 days).  Concurrent. 
Term of Probation: 2 Years
Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Disclose to any physician in writing your probation conditions
Sign Medical Release for Agent;
Seek employment;
Condition Time: 5 days jail without Huber, consecutive: STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion
Restitution: $300.00 to be paid to Landmark Credit Union as a condition of probation
COSTS:  $253.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
